results.original_title: Robot Chicken: Star Wars Episode II
results.overview: Seth Green and Matthew Senreich serve up more hilarious Star Wars-inspired satire in this second compilation of sketches featuring the zany stop-motion animation of Adult Swim's "Robot Chicken." Gary the stormtrooper deals with irascible boss Darth Vader on Take Your Daughter to Work Day, while Anakin babysits a certain up-and-coming Jedi. Carrie Fisher, Billy Dee Williams, Conan O'Brien and other stars provide voices.
results.title: Robot Chicken: Star Wars Episode II

results.original_title: Star Wars Rebels: Spark of Rebellion
results.overview: Ezra Bridger encounters the Ghost crew and joins them on a mission to free Wookiees from an Imperial Star Destroyer.
results.title: Star Wars Rebels: Spark of Rebellion

results.overview: The imperial forces of Lord Quimio capture princess Felelia and steal a big cargo of vital force for the rebellion. Obi Wan Quequena, warned by the princess, starts gathering a group of brave people to recover the force, save the princess and end the empire that strikes the galaxy.
results.title: Star Wars: Goretech

results.overview: Actor Ian McDiarmid introduces several music videos scored by the infamous Star Wars scores composed by John Williams. There are sixteen chapters in all, and are all perfectly created to show us the great music from the six films.
results.title: Star Wars: A Musical Journey

results.original_title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars - Darth Maul Returns
results.overview: After Dathomir falls prey to a merciless attack by General Grievous, Asajj Ventress survives to join a bounty hunter clan led by a young Boba Fett. Meanwhile, the dark warrior Savage Opress returns to his creator, the witch Mother Talzin, who gives him a sinister mission: to search the galaxy for his brother, Sith Apprentice Darth Maul. Believed dead for over a decade after falling to the sword of then Jedi Apprentice Obi-Wan Kenobi, Darth Maul is nearly unrecognizable, residing in the bowels of a ruined planet and fueled by hatred. Savage Opress delivers the shattered Maul to Mother Talzin to restore his former powers, and the brothers vow an oath of vengeance against Obi-Wan Kenobi.
results.title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars - Darth Maul Returns

results.original_title: Star Wars Rebels: The Siege of Lothal
results.overview: The Ghost crew and their allies face Darth Vader for the first time and Ahsoka Tano discovers the true identity of Darth Vader.
results.title: Star Wars Rebels: The Siege of Lothal

results.overview: The farce is strong with this one! Enjoy a hilarious collection of Star Wars movie scene spoofs and parodies that have been created over the years, including outrageous clips from Family Guy, The Simpsons, How I Met Your Mother, and more - and don't miss "Weird Al" Yankovic's one-of-a-kind music video tribute to The Phantom Menace!
results.title: Star Wars Spoofs

results.overview: Film-makers and academics discuss the use of mythology in Star Wars and the impact of the films on society
results.title: Star Wars: The Legacy Revealed

results.overview: In “Entanglement,” a special Star Wars Rebels short, Zeb fails to meet with Kanan at a specified rendezvous point…and instead finds himself joyfully battling many, many stormtroopers.
results.title: Star Wars Rebels: Entanglement

results.overview: This is a very interesting Star Wars documentary about the making of the first Star Wars film (and to a lesser extent Empire and Jedi) including a look at some of the deleted scenes, behind the scenes footage, and notes on subtle things that you might have never seen or noticed before.
results.title: Star Wars: Deleted Magic

results.overview: Learn the incredible behind-the-scenes story of how the original Star Wars  movie was brought to the big screen in this fascinating documentary hosted by C-3PO and R2-D2 which includes interviews with George Lucas and appearances by Mark Hamill, Harrison Ford and Carrie Fisher.
results.title: The Making of Star Wars

results.original_title: Empire of Dreams: The Story of the Star Wars Trilogy
results.overview: From the earliest versions of the script to the blockbuster debuts, explore the creation of the Star Wars Trilogy.
results.title: Empire of Dreams: The Story of the Star Wars Trilogy

results.original_title: LEGO Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Out
results.overview: Luke Skywalker embarks on a mission to destroy a Imperial base, but is relentlessly chased by a group of fanatic girls who think of him as a celebrity. Meanwhile, Darth Vader engages a rivalry with Darth Maul, in order to prove that he's the best Sith Lord.
results.title: LEGO Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Out

results.original_title: Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge - Adventure Awaits
results.overview: An exclusive behind-the-scenes look at the new lands at Walt Disney World Resort in Florida and Disneyland Resort in Southern California.
results.title: Star Wars: Galaxy's Edge - Adventure Awaits

results.overview: Exploring the technical aspects of Star Wars vehicles, weapons and gadgetry, Star Wars Tech consults leading scientists in the fields of physics, prosthetics, lasers, engineering and astronomy to examine the plausibility of Star Wars technology based on science as we know it today.
results.title: Star Wars Tech

results.overview: Darth Vader hires Boba Fett to track down Jar Jar Binks, who has caused a lot of trouble for Vader. Will Jar Jar escape the wrath of the Empire - or will he ultimately be captured?
results.title: LEGO Star Wars: Bombad Bounty

results.original_title: Star Wars Rebels: Steps Into Shadow
results.overview: Ezra, having grown in power, leads a mission to break the crew's old friend Hondo Ohnaka out of prison. Meanwhile, Grand Admiral Thrawn -- a master Imperial strategist -- has vowed to dismantle and destroy the growing rebellion.
results.title: Star Wars Rebels: Steps Into Shadow

results.original_title: When Star Wars Ruled the World
results.overview: That time when Star Wars Ruled the World, the cast discuss what made it a phenomenon.
results.title: When Star Wars Ruled the World

results.overview: The Characters of Star Wars is a Video Documentary included in the 2004 DVD release of the Star Wars Original Trilogy. It explained the Mythos of many of the "Star Wars" Characters.
results.title: The Characters of Star Wars
